27/07/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Security Minister Barisa Colak announced on Tuesday (26 July) that a national strategy for combating terrorism would be ready by year's end. He said a task force, including representatives of the BiH government, all security and intelligence structures in the country as well as the BiH Prosecutor's Office, is working on a draft. 
In other news Tuesday, the BiH State Border Service received a donation worth 200,000 euros from Germany, aimed at strengthening border control. The German Interior Ministry delivered computers, software and equipment for identifying forged documents. (RTRS, PBS BiH - 26/07/05)
